About This Project  

Enhanced TELEports is a community-driven project built upon the work of Dan Chapman and the UBports Foundation. It is designed to provide a free and open-source Telegram client for Ubuntu Touch, ensuring seamless communication without any restrictions.  

This project is fully open-source, and no individual or organization claims ownership over it. Anyone is free to use, modify, or distribute it without limitations.  

---

Third-Party Dependencies  

Enhanced TELEports relies on:  

- [TDLib (Telegram Database Library)](https://github.com/tdlib/td) – an official Telegram library for backend operations and communication with Telegram servers. Licensed under the Boost Software License.  

- Ubuntu Touch Frameworks – maintained by the UBports Foundation, ensuring compatibility with Ubuntu Touch OS.  

